PURPOSE:-
--------
To show the operation of demand circuit in ospfv2 in a four-node 
network and all ospfv2 routers supports demand circuit except one router.



SCENARIO:-
---------
In this scenario, there is one CBR session, with node 1 being the source
and node 4 being the destination.  The link capacity is 2Mbps.

             DC
1 ------- 2--------3--------4
   2Mbps    2Mbps    2Mbps
   
   
APPLICATION:-
-----------

CBR is used to transfer 600 data segments of 512B each at 5 second intervals
starting at 20 minutes to 30 minutes.


DEMAND CIRCUIT CONFIGURATION:-
-------------------------------
Node 2 supports DC
Node 3 supports DC
Node 4 supports DC
LINK (2,3) is a DC


RUN:-
----

Run '<QUALNET_HOME>/bin/qualnet    single-area-all-DC-except-1.config'.


DESCRIPTION OF THE FILES:-
-------------------------
1. single-area-all-DC-except-1.app -  QualNet application configuration file
2. single-area-all-DC-except-1.config - QualNet configuration input file.
3. single-area-all-DC-except-1.stat - QualNet statistics collection for CBR and OSPFv2.
4. single-area-all-DC-except-1.ospf - OSPFv2 configuration input file.
5. README - This file.

